# Lab Screenshots — Step-by-Step Walkthrough

Visual evidence of each phase of the pfSense DoS Defense lab, in order of execution.

---

## Step 1 — pfSense Console: Interface Assignment & Firewall Disable

![pfSense Console](screenshots/08-pfsense-console-pfctl.png)

**What this shows:**
- pfSense 2.8.1-RELEASE running in VirtualBox
- Interface assignment confirmed: `WAN (wan) → em0 → v4/DHCP4: 192.168.1.6/24`
- Interface assignment confirmed: `LAN (lan) → em1 → v4: 192.168.10.1/24`
- Shell option `8` selected to enter the pfSense shell
- Command `pfctl -d` executed to temporarily disable the pfSense packet filter
- Output `pf disabled` confirms the firewall was disabled to allow initial WebGUI access from the WAN side

